snippet.textDisplay:
## For those who want to know the "Meaning". 

The term "Khalasi" in Gujarati signifies a sailor of the boat who ventures into the stormy ocean, rather than staying on the shore. This journey requires the individual to overcome their own fears and, most importantly, their limited view of the world. The lyricist emphasizes that taking risks as an individual and exploring one's inner self is just as crucial as being a human being. 

The motivation from the lyricist is not to confine oneself to the view from the shore, which limits one's perception of the world. Instead, they encourage people to look deep within themselves. On the shore, you can only take small steps, but within the ocean, there are boundless opportunities. These opportunities are unexplored and unknown to your mind, with the possibility of discovering something new. 

Challenges are seen as an integral part of understanding oneself, and taking risks is necessary to explore these possibilities. Without taking risks, you cannot unlock these opportunities. By taking risks, you can uncover your true worth, which is described as "invaluable."
